items.name: Eerie Mix of Decay
items.description:
A change of pace from thee cutesy and created this horror model by chance. This makes a wide range of creepy creatures that fuel nightmares.

How to use recommendations:

- Clip skip: 2

- CFG scale: 4-12

- Sampler: Euler A, DPM++2M SDE Karras, UniPC

- Sampling Steps : 20-40

- Upscaler (Hires. fix): R-ESRGAN 4x+, 4x-UltraSharp, Latent (nearest), Latent (bicubic)

- Hires steps: 10-24

- Denoising strength: 0.3-0.5

- Dimensions: 768x512 or 512x768

- Upscale by: 2.5+

- Positive: (high quality, masterpiece), terms related to horror (horror, spooky, frightening, etc). Also creatures such as zombie, skeleton, demon, witch, etc..

- Negative: (low quality, signature, watermark), ...

- Use aDetailer to fix the faces

  • Use face_yolov8n.pt

- Recommended VAE: Yozora or any of your choice, but you need to choose one as there is no baked in VAE

Credit:

Samaritan 3d Cartoon by @PromptSharingSamaritan

Ether Real Mix by @gamerdan69

Night Sky YOZORA Style Model by @YozoRaAru

VodkaMix by @advokat

items.name: Realistic Persian Girls
items.description:
This is the first successful LoRA training attemp I have had on Dreambooth and I unfortunately was not able to train it on SDXL but I'll try training an SDXL version sometime in the future,(It's based on SD1.5)

When I wanted to create a Persian girl in Stable Diffusion They would look more Indian than Persian so I decided to train my own LoRa to have better results.

It is not perfect and I haven't tested it a lot but in my limited testing I got relatively good results.

The dataset was trained of public pictures of random Persian girls and some of my friends with their permission.

Edit: If you see artifacts on the face, lower the weight and put it from 0.6 to 0.8, if this doesn't fix it send the output to image to image then use empty prompt and low Denoising strength to fix those issues, I hope to find a way to make it better in future versions.

items.name: FoolKat GOD-OF-BEAUTY
items.description:
This is the eighteenth model in my God series.

You can find all the models at GOD-OF-GREED, GOD-OF-ENVY, GOD-OF-LOVE, GOD-OF-ANIME, GOD-OF-LUST, GOD-OF-JUSTICE, GOD-OF-TIME, GOD-OF-FANTASY, GOD-OF-JOY, GOD-OF-HORROR, GOD-OF-PRIDE, GOD-OF-PUNK, GOD-OF-STORMS, GOD-OF-EUPHORIA, GOD-OF-GLUTTONY, GOD-OF-THE-WEST, GOD-OF-BEAUTY, GOD-OF-SEDUCTION, and GOD-OF-PEACE.

This model was a happy accident that occurred while making my GOD-OF-PRIDE model. I ended up with a beta version of that model that worked well when mixed with a couple of style loras designed to give a "beauty" aesthetic. This model tends to create absolutely gorgeous artwork, especially for female subjects, that look majestic and sensual without being sexual, so it is sort of the opposite side of the coin to my GOD-OF-LUST model.

The model has Blessed2 VAE baked into it, so no VAE required.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.

items.name: Pam Grier (1970-78 era - LORA)
items.description:
Shivam Dreambooth>LORA of American actress Pam Grier, using 92 ref images and 1400 (real) reg images, for 9,000 steps. Will default to stock-style poses, and may well produce subject-accurate NSFW output unless countered in negative prompts.

NOTE: This particular model is a little overcooked, so keep the CFG level low. For T2I generation, try clip skip 2 if general results unsatisfactory in terms of diversity.

I generally use these models in complex workflows, inpainting faces after initial T2Is, and using ControlNet extensively. So if you're hoping for one-click prompt magic, my models aren't data-curated with this in mind, but rather as tools for traditional workflows that use Photoshop and other older methods.

items.name: PaizuriAIO (all-in-one)
items.description:
The Trigger word has negative effects sometimes, try genning with and without it, especially if going for nongeneric breast squeeze paizuri; IE: breast suppress, breast lift, etc (for V2, not sure how helpful this is on V1 since i have fixed and gathered a lot more images/captions)

I am finalizing V2, should update in a day or two hopefully - august 8th

this is a remake of my older (bad) all purpose paizuri model = PaizuriAllinOne (different angles and types). This is not a repository or merge of my Loras, I may try and merge some loras into this on though.

V1 is trained on 447 images with at least half of the captions edited and the rest i glossed over. plan to add more images and better captions in later versions. Can use with my breasts apart and breast lift models, along with others.

weights 0.7 - 1.0

some versions may work better at different dimensions. CHECK BELOW THE PAIZURI VARIATION FOR VARIATION TAGS AND HELPFUL TAGS

important tags: uncensored

negative: bar censor, mosaic censoring, censored

more than half the dataset is uncensored and it seems to default to uncensored for me, but just in case add these.

so far the variations include:

paizuri,

double/triple/More? paizuri,

straddling paizuri (man on top)

fellatio/licking paizuri (really iffy),

lying paizuri (girl on stomach. very little in the dataset so is extremely hard to get correct)

paizuri under clothes,

paizuri over clothes,

shortstack/standing paizuri (pretty hard to get)

perpendicular paizuri (kind of weird doesn't seem to work correctly, it likes to curve the penis near the tip to correct it, but it is possible to get a perpendicular paizuri, just not as easily as the others, will try and improve).

variation tags: breast lift, breast suppress, no hands, breasts squeezed together, elbow squeeze, unaligned breasts, bukkake, excessive cum, pov, from side, from front, from above, from below, multiple views, breast grab, close-up, oral, licking penis, motion blur, motion lines, breast hold. after paizuri, breasts apart, long penis, large penis, arm up, arms up, arm grab, wrist grab

some tag explanations

breast lift: hands under breasts lifting them up

no hands: paizuri with no hands, works best with straddling paizuri (adding arm up/arms up) helps.

elbow squeeze: should probably be named wrist squeeze, either way, it's when the breasts are pushed together by the arms (can work),

breasts suppress: hands pushing breast down,

breast grab: tried to link it to man/pov grabbing the breasts,

bukkake: lots of cum,

excessive cum: more than bukkake (not sure if it actually works),

breast hold: arm in front of nipples squeezing the breasts, adding arm under breasts should put them under so the breasts are resting on them, (seems to like to gen from below without reinforcing prompt; i got it to work by adding "covering nipples, covering breasts" to the positive and putting "arms under breasts" in the negative)

After paizuri: works best with straddling paizuri and a lower weight; the penis resting in/above the cleavage usually with cum, for the example of this i added "penis in cleavage" and used my breasts apart Lora, it works without it just liked the results better.

mixing the variation tags and the paizuri types should give different results. I'm not sure if not adding any allows any of them to happen.

not sure how it works with other models, should work with characters at least.

some of these are iffy and some may not work, added a lot of the variation tags to images that had them, but plenty i was too tired to edit. from my testing unaligned breasts was a nightmare to get, will probably just make a all purpose unaligned breast model, along with other things that it struggles to do on it's own.

random errors: penis turns into neck bell sometimes if using it in prompt/a character that has one ie: ganyu.

items.name: Hairy Men
items.description:
LoRA to make men hairy(ier) except it makes them look melted too :)

  • The images on each page don't correlate to the model I'm dumb and didn't realise they weren't shared 😭please forgive me

\/ IMPORTANT NOTE \/

There are three versions offered, all of them bad but slightly different:

-AlrightALT (Recommended): NEW™ It's the same as Alright but I nuked half the blocks. Now should no longer effect the style of the image, and can be used as a pseudo-slider. More dependant on "hairy" being in positive or negative prompts as a result. Probably the last release maybe.

- Alright: Like okay but better. Probably as good as it's going to get without me getting a better collection of hairy men images. No TE training like Okay either.

- Okay: A more standard, usable LoRA. The effects are there but they're less face-melty. Will still impact pose and introduce nudity. Has no text encoder training so you don't need to turn that down. Effects are less noticeable but doesn't immediately deepfry your gens.

- Okay_ALT: Like okay but I like it sliiightly better.

- Bad: Doesn't have as strong of a melting effect on the overall style of the image, but isn't as pronounced

- Worse: Middleground, degrades image style but not as noticeably, is mostly usable in txt2img

- Worst: Degrades the entire image quality, still usable if you img2img from it as a base

Overall I recommend lowering strength_clip for best results since I am ape brained.

Known issues

I'm aware it looks like garbage, destroys faces, reduces image quality etc. This is because I have no idea what I'm doing.

It also will push towards more tanned skin, I tried to remedy this in the dataset by including some gingers but :shrug:. The poses also trend towards more front facing angles, and the majority of the dataset was nudes so it also trends towards that.

How do I get results that look like the preview images?

img2img is a must until I stop being lazy and tag thing better/get a better dataset. I recommend grabbing ComfyUI and setting up samplers with the LoRA at different strengths (or one with one without), ending with a higher CFG to define the image out.

Feel free to message me on discord @fleshtexture if you'd like help
